The paper discusses the use of Massive MIMO technology in wireless communications, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Augmented Reality (cs.AR). The paper specifically addresses misunderstandings and myths surrounding Massive MIMO, which suggests a focus on the technical aspects of the technology, making cs.IT and cs.NI the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also touches on implementation challenges and future research directions, which could fall under cs.SY and cs.MM. The mention of augmented reality in the abstract also suggests a potential connection to cs.AR.
